==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swelter
<hw>Swel"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Sweltered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Sweltering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From <er>Swelt</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To be overcome and faint with
heat; to be ready to perish with heat.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sweltered</xex>
cattle.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To welter; to soak.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swelter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swelter
<hw>Swel"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To oppress with
heat.</def> <rj><au>Bentley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exude, like sweat.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweltry</ent>⟦br⟧
